way win   = \n  | highest scoring    = \n  | matches            = \n  | total goals        = \n  | longest wins       = \n  | longest unbeaten   = \n  | longest losses     = \n  | highest attendance = \n  | lowest attendance  = \n  | average attendance = \n  | prevseason         = [[1995\u201396 Ukrainian First League|1995\u201396]]\n  | nextseason         = [[1997\u201398 Ukrainian First League|1997\u201398]]\n}}\n'''1996\u201397 Ukrainian First League''' was the sixth season of the [[Ukrainian First League]] which was won by [[Metalurh Donetsk]]. The season started on August 4, 1996, and finished on June 20, 1997.\n\n==Promotion and relegation==\n===Promoted teams===\nThree clubs promoted from the [[1995\u201396 Ukrainian Second League]].\n;Group A\n* [[FC CSKA Kyiv]] &ndash; champion ''(returning after four seasons, previously in 1992 as SKA Kiev)''\n;Group B\n* [[FC Illichivets Mariupol|FC Metalurh Mariupol]] &ndash; champion ''(returning after four seasons, previously in 1992 as FC Azovets Mariupol)''\n* [[FC Metalurh Donetsk]] &ndash; promotion play-off ''(debut)''\n\n=== Relegated teams ===\nThree clubs were relegated from the [[1995-96 Ukrainian Premier League|1995-96 Ukrainian Top League]]:\n* [[SC Mykolaiv]] &ndash; 16th place ''(returning after two seasons, previously in 1994-95 as FC Evis Mykolaiv)''\n* [[FC Volyn Lutsk]] &ndash; 17th place ''(debut)''\n* [[FC Zorya Luhansk]] &ndash; 18th place ''(debut)''\n\n===Renamed teams===\n* FC Zakarpattia Uzhhorod changed its name to '''FC Verkhovyna Uzhhorod''' before the season.\n* FC CSKA Kyiv changed its name to '''FC CSKA-2 Kyiv''' before the season since becoming the farm team of the Borysfen-CSKA merger.\n* FC Dnipro Cherkasy changed its name to '''FC Cherkasy''' during the winter break.\n\n===Teams===\nIn 1996-97 season, the Ukrainian First League consists of the following teams:\n{{Location map+|Ukraine|AlternativeMap = Ukraine (1991-2014) location map.svg|width=900|float=center|caption=Locations of teams in '''First League'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=49.916667 |long=36.316667 |label=[[FC Metalist Kharkiv|Metalist]] }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=50.25     |long=28.666667 |label=[[FC Polissya Zhytomyr|Khimik]]|position=left }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=50.45     |long=30.523333 |label=[[FC Dynamo-2 Kyiv|Dynamo-2]]|position=bottom }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=50.45     |long=30.523333 |label=[[FC CSKA Kyiv|CSKA-2]]|position=top }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=50.616667 |long=26.25     |label=[[FC Veres Rivne|Veres]]|position=right }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=49.85     |long=24.016667 |label=[[FC Lviv (1992)|Lviv]]|position=right }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=49.416667 |long=27.0      |label=[[FC Podillya Khmelnytskyi|Podillya]]|position=right }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=49.016667 |long=25.8      |label=[[FC Krystal Chortkiv|Krystal]]|position=right }} \n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=50.716667 |long=34.95     |label=[[FC Yavir Krasnopilya|Yavir]]|position=bottom }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=48.566667 |long=39.333333 |label=[[FC Zoria Luhansk|Zoria]]|position=top }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=49.433333 |long=32.066667 |label=[[FC Dnipro Cherkasy|Cherkasy]] |position=left }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=50.75     |long=33.466667 |label=[[FC Naftovyk-Ukrnafta Okhtyrka|Naftovyk]]|position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=48.083333 |long=38.066667 |label=[[FC Shakhtar Makiivka|Shakhtar]]|position=right }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=48.666667 |long=33.116667 |label=[[PFC Olexandria|Polihraftekhnika]]|position=bottom }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=48.466667 |long=38.8      |label=[[FC Stal Alchevsk|Stal]]|position=left }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=48.616667 |long=22.3      |label=[[FC Zakarpattia Uzhhorod|Zakarpattia]]|position=right }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=47.566667 |long=34.4      |label=[[FC Elektrometalurh-NZF Nikopol|Metalurh N.]]|position=right }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=50.75     |long=25.335833 |label=[[FC Volyn Lutsk|Volyn]]|position=top }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=46.966667 |long=32.0      |label=[[MFK Mykolaiv|Mykolaiv]]|position=top }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=47.116667 |long=37.55     |label=[[FC Illychivets Mariupol|Metalurh M.]]|position=left }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=48.000278 |long=37.805278 |label=[[FC Metalurh Donetsk|Metalurh D.]]|position=left }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=48.933333 |long=38.5      |label=[[FC Khimik Severodonetsk|Khimik]]|position=left }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=46.466667 |long=30.733333 |label=[[SCA Odessa|Odessa]]|position=bottom }}\n{{Location map~|Ukraine|lat=48.3      |long=25.933333 |label=[[FC Bukovyna Chernivtsi|Bukovyna]]|position=left }}\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Club !! City !! Stadium !! Coach !! Replaced coach(es)\n|-\n| [[FC Metalist Kharkiv|Metalist Kharkiv]] || [[Kharkiv]] || [[Metalist Stadium]] || [[Mykhailo Fomenko]] || Viktor Udovenko\n|-\n| [[FC Veres Rivne|Veres Rivne]] || [[Rivne]] || Avanhard Stadium || Viacheslav Kobeletsky || \n|-\n| [[PFC Olexandria|Poligraftechnika Olexandria]] || [[Oleksandriya]] || Olimp Stadium || [[Yuriy Koval]] || [[Anatoliy Buznyk]]\n|-\n| [[FC Podillya Khmelnytskyi|Podillya Khmelnytskyi]] || [[Khmelnytskyi, Ukraine|Khmelnytskyi]]<br>[[Krasyliv]] || Podillya Stadium<br>Yunist Stadium || V.Kvartsyany || Volodymyr Bulhakov\n|-\n| [[FC Krystal Chortkiv|Krystal Chortkiv]] || [[Chortkiv]] || Kharchovyk Stadium || V.Ivehesh || [[Ivan Hamaliy]]\n|-\n| [[FC Lviv (1992)|Lviv]] || [[Lviv]] || [[Yunist Stadium (Lviv)|Yunist Stadium]] || [[Stepan Yurchyshyn]] || \n|-\n| [[FC Dynamo-2 Kyiv|Dynamo-2 Kyiv]] || [[Kyiv]] || Dynamo Stadium || [[Volodymyr Onyshchenko]] || \n|-\n| [[FC Spartak Sumy|Yavir Krasnopillia]] || [[Krasnopillya]] || Kolos Stadium<br>Yavir Stadium || [[Valeriy Dushkov]] || \n|-\n| [[FC Stal Alchevsk|Stal Alchevsk]] || [[Alchevsk]] || Stal Stadium || [[Anatoliy Volobuyev]] || \n|-\n| [[FC Dnipro Cherkasy|Dnipro Cherkasy]] || [[Cherkasy]] || Central Stadium<br>S